The synthesized CCDs present one characteristic brown powder,as shown in inset of Fig. 1 a. In the X-ray diffraction pattern (Fig. 1a) of CCDs, one stronger broad peak is observed at 2θ = 20° and another weaker peak at 2θ = 41°, which correspond to the (002) and (100) planes of graphitic carbon, characterizing the abundant SP3 disorder and low degree of graphitization in CCDs [29]. The d-spacing was calculated to be 4.43 Å for the (002) plane using the Bragg equation (
2 dsin θ = n λ
). Compared to the 3.3 Å d-spacing of bulk graphite [29], the higher d-spacing value of CCDs suggests that the SCG undergo random crystallization during the carbonization process where the synthesized CCDs is not highly graphitized and exhibits a partial graphitization structure, or even tends towards an amorphous state [30].The CCDs could be well dispersed in ethanol and no precipitate appeared after standing for 2 h. Fig. 1b shows the TEM image of the CCDs powder, and one can see that the CCDs particles are evenly dispersed and appear quasi-spherical, with an average size of 19.15 nm.
